Yes — clap supports `#[command(flatten)]` which lets you define a shared args struct and embed it in each subcommand. Something like:

```rust
// common.rs
#[derive(Args, Debug)]
pub struct RepoArgs {
    #[arg(short = 'R', long = "repo", value_name = "PATH")]
    pub repos: Vec<PathBuf>,

    #[arg(short = 'l', long = "label", ..., default_value = "===")]
    pub label: String,

    #[arg(short = 'L', long = "no-label")]
    pub no_label: bool,
}

// chid.rs
pub struct ChidArgs {
    #[command(flatten)]
    pub repo: RepoArgs,

    // chid-specific args...
}
```

That would deduplicate `-R`, `-l`, `-L`, `-r`, `-n`, and the positional args too. Good cleanup but separate from 0.21.0 — add it as a todo?

